race.comment: CHANTILLY'S STAR (7) rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (22.56) at Ballarat over 390m. Expected to feature in the finish again. PAW BENNETT (1) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing second (23.03) and beaten 0.8 lengths over 400m at this track. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Will give a great sight again. ASTON KILLARA (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (23.39) last time in a R/A FIN at this track. Likely to play a prominent role. UNDERSHOT VALMA (5) warrants respect although new to this track.
